fieldMappings.name: Block External Quantity
fieldMappings.description: Setting this flag to true will prevent listing and fulfillment from externally managed distribution centers (DCs).

fieldMappings.name: DC Quantity
fieldMappings.description:
Use this field to set different quantity amounts for your item in different distribution centers (DCs) You must follow the following convention to use this field:
{ DC Code 1}={ Quantity for DC1}, { DC Code 2}={ Quantity for DC2}, ...
For example: NYC = 1, Atlanta = 3
Only values for distribution centers you manage will be allowed. Any values for externally managed distribution centers, such as Amazon FBA, will result in a warning for that item, with the quantity update for that distribution center ignored.If you supply one or more values for this column, any values specified in the 'Quantity' column will be ignored.

fieldMappings.name: DC Quantity Update Type
fieldMappings.description:
Complete DC List - this will set the DC Quantity, wiping out any DC quantity not submitted.
Partial DC List - this will set the DC Quantity, ignoring any DC quantity not submitted.
Single DC Quantity - this will maintain backwards compatibility, MOVING quantity from one DC to another.
Once you have used Complete or Partial, you can not go back to Single DC Quantity.

fieldMappings.name: DC Code
fieldMappings.description: Distribution Center Code

fieldMappings.name: Quantity
fieldMappings.description: Quantity available for your product.

fieldMappings.name: Quantity Update Type
fieldMappings.description:
Type of quantity update to perform. There are 5 accepted values. If this item is new to ChannelAdvisor, the Quantity Update Type is irrelevant. This field is required if the SKU already exists in ChannelAdvisor Complete.
ABSOLUTE sets the inventory quantity for this item to the value of the uploaded quantity.
RELATIVE adds the value of the uploaded quantity to the current inventory quantity.Negative numbers are accepted in the upload.
AVAILABLE takes the upload value of quantity, subtracts out any open auctions for this SKU and sets the remaining value as the inventory quantity.
IN STOCK takes the upload value of quantity, subtracts out any open auctions, pending checkouts, and pending payments for this SKU and sets the remaining value as the inventory quantity.
UNSHIPPED takes the upload value of quantity, subtracts out any open auctions, pending checkouts, pending payments and pending shipments for this SKU and sets the remaining value as the inventory quantity.
